{"TopicId":182531,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Three Ton Speed Run","CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-28T20:28:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Ultimate Steve","CreatedById":161505,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-28T20:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nWelcome to the Three Ton Speed Run! It\u0027s exactly like the Twenty Ton Speed Run, but with a lower mass limit, because the 20t escalated quickly, exceeding 30 kilometers per second, I feel like a limit of 3 tons would make the challenge more accessible. Both challenges will continue to run, however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nYour goal is to take a craft that masses no more than 3 tons (including EVA Kerbals and not including any launch clamps) and reach the highest velocity possible, relative to Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nFairly simple, so I think I can get away with not submitting something as it\u0027s fairly obvious that this challenge is possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nRules:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n3 ton limit includes EVA Kerbals and not launch clamps. Don\u0027t abuse the launch clamps.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nVelocity is measured using the \u0022orbital\u0022 setting on the navball.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nYou may not leave Kerbin\u0027s\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Efor the challenge. You may be on an escape trajectory at the end, but you can\u0027t measure your velocity outside Kerbin\u0027s\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cabbr style=\u0022border-bottom:none;\u0022 title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eor leave before measurement.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAccidental Mun/Minmus encounters are alright, but try to avoid them.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nStock and Making History only, although non physics changing mods may be installed, and other parts mods may be installed but not used. Mods which allow faster physics warp are okay.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIn general try to not exploit stuff. No debug menu, .sfs editing, HyperEdit, Kraken drives, etc.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nProof required is a screenshot at or near your highest velocity. Other screenshots showing your vehicle and how it works are required, unless you have a video.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThere will be separate leaderboards for manned and unmanned entries.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nLeaderboards:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nManned:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nUnmanned:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\nHave fun!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-28T20:36:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood challenge. For folks who don\u0027t know, EVA Kerbals are 0.9375 tons, and their \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E propellant is massless.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dnbattley","CreatedById":176526,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-02T21:20:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGetting my marker in to this challenge quickly, since I am absolutely sure it will be comprehensively beaten: manned @ \u003Cs\u003E3,678\u003C/s\u003E \u003Cs\u003E3,860\u003C/s\u003E\u00A03,880 m/s, after EVA.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT - updated with latest run, in which I tweaked the fuel loads slightly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224nv3Uzf.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/4nv3Uzf.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2.991T - whiplash lower stage, with\u00A0spark upper stage and command seat\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Fh7zMop.png?1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022646\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Fh7zMop.png?1\u0022 width=\u0022693\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBetter view of interior\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022T6gcLmm.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/T6gcLmm.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-02T22:02:32Z\u0022 title=\u002203/02/2019 10:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 2, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by dnbattley\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xurkitree","CreatedById":187694,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-03T04:01:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did some thinking on this and its better to go into an hyperbolic trajectory against Kwrbin rotation to get more orbital speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dnbattley","CreatedById":176526,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-03T20:27:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223550666\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182531\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221551585663\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187694\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xurkitree\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Xurkitree said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did some thinking on this and its better to go into an hyperbolic trajectory against Kwrbin rotation to get more orbital speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis would be true for surface speed, but the orbital speed going counter-clockwise and clockwise is identical: it just needs more delta-v to get there against the rotation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dnbattley","CreatedById":176526,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-04T23:39:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSurpassed my previous with a slightly different design, this time managing to get an ion craft into orbit, and ultimately posting a new manned speed of \u003Cs\u003E4,186\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003E4,390\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0m/s, which, unless I make major changes is probably about as far as I can push this design, although I note that the flight path (particularly in the first few seconds) is such a\u00A0critical determinant for final speed that 100 additional tries \u003Cem\u003Emay\u003C/em\u003E yield a better result.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gOejYcN.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/gOejYcN.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EForgive the lack of naming while I played around with this. In fact I now realise I forgot to remove the launch clamp weight so will be able to improve on this further (but not tonight), but 2.998T as shown. Let\u0027s assume this will be named the \u00223T Flyer Mk II\u0022\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow properly named, the \u00223T Flyer Mk II Rev A\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022dDmVteo.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/dDmVteo.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEnergy was at a premium, meaning short burns as far as possible, but here after all Xenon depleted we surpassed \u003Cs\u003E4k\u003C/s\u003E 4.1k, then got out...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tVzUIvK.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/tVzUIvK.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd thus \u003Cs\u003E4,186\u003C/s\u003E\u00A04,390 m/s recorded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-05T10:00:39Z\u0022 title=\u002203/05/2019 10:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 5, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by dnbattley\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EImproved times, again.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"joshudson","CreatedById":123912,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-06T06:18:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI see your 4390 and raise you 619 for a new speed of 5009 m/s. \u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/i2oAw3W\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/i2oAw3W\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Magzimum","CreatedById":167187,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-08T21:33:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWithout using Valentina\u0027s jetpack, I got her to go 2829.2 m/s, on a chemical rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022lnGZ1bH.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/lnGZ1bH.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, it\u0027s a 3-stage rocket. Bottom stage is only fuel, no engines, and the bottom is not 100% full to stay within the mass limits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ZJgfZDP.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/ZJgfZDP.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunch is uneventful, although it looks a little dinky.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022l7bpgLg.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/l7bpgLg.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClimbed out of the atmosphere with the fairing still on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022LAGTuSR.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/LAGTuSR.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen went for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E on 3 tiny engines.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022GVQuECR.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/GVQuECR.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen increased Apoapsis, lowered periapsis to 60 km, for even more speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022oXFiNDR.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/oXFiNDR.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd took the photo above for the top speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wish I could say that this can be optimized further, but getting a Kerbal into orbit with a limit of 3 tons is actually already quite the challenge for me. I really enjoyed it! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"astrobond","CreatedById":127649,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T10:23:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi all \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0a little more than 3700m/s in escape orbit with this rocket on the first try but could be better with a good last PE burn and better flight plan... xD :\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022p6k5FSV.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/p6k5FSV.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022O3yiwGu.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/O3yiwGu.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFly safe with Valentina \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-03-10T12:30:34Z\u0022 title=\u002203/10/2019 12:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 10, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by astrobond\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"astrobond","CreatedById":127649,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T12:23:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSame rocket, my best try 4935m/s (without jetpack)... not enough to have the high score lol grrrr \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mmw170R.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/mmw170R.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFly safe with Valentina \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"astrobond","CreatedById":127649,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-03-10T17:35:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was so close... so i replaced the 700 xenon tank by 2 x 400, new fairing to keep the weight ok with valentina onboard to be under 3T, and.... 5189m/s xD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022cHOQV3J.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/cHOQV3J.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u0022new\u0022 rocket:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022HIOhH74.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/HIOhH74.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFly safe with Valentina \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}